530
00:05:11.250 --> 00:05:15.210
Head captain and one of
the Four Emperors, Straw Hat Luffy.

531
00:05:15.210 --> 00:05:18.460
Bounty: 3 billion berries!

532
00:05:20.590 --> 00:05:22.470
I'm hungry...

533
00:05:23.260 --> 00:05:25.930
Empty Bluffs Island

534
00:05:25.930 --> 00:05:27.010
Did ya see 'em?

535
00:05:27.010 --> 00:05:28.350
You bet I did!

536
00:05:28.350 --> 00:05:29.890
It was really them!

537
00:05:29.890 --> 00:05:31.390
Man!

538
00:05:33.860 --> 00:05:37.320
That was the world's greatest
swordsman?! He's scary!

539
00:05:37.320 --> 00:05:38.730
For real!

540
00:05:41.780 --> 00:05:47.910
When the Seven Warlords were abolished and those
Marine ships came, I thought we were done for.

541
00:05:49.200 --> 00:05:53.170
We should've known President Buggy
would turn things around!

542
00:05:57.090 --> 00:06:00.670
Please stop!

543
00:06:00.670 --> 00:06:04.890
I-I'll give you anything if you let me live!

544
00:06:06.260 --> 00:06:08.600
I'm begging you!

545
00:06:08.600 --> 00:06:10.220
I'll do anything!

546
00:06:10.220 --> 00:06:13.810
Emperor Buggy "the Bombastic Clown"

547
00:06:10.600 --> 00:06:13.810
I'll even lick your boots clean! Please!

548
00:06:15.100 --> 00:06:18.570
Former Warlord Sir Crocodile

549
00:06:19.320 --> 00:06:25.110
Mihawk and I were the ones who
first planned to form Cross Guild.

550
00:06:22.280 --> 00:06:25.700
Former Warlord Dracule Mihawk

551
00:06:25.700 --> 00:06:29.090
And now you're the boss? Well, Buggy?

552
00:06:29.090 --> 00:06:32.500
All I can do is say I'm sorry!

553
00:06:32.500 --> 00:06:34.120
And please overlook this!

554
00:06:35.120 --> 00:06:40.460
You're the first and last person in history
to become Emperor by sniveling for mercy.

555
00:06:40.960 --> 00:06:43.760
Keeping you alive would set a bad precedent.

556
00:06:46.010 --> 00:06:51.430
This is beyond embarrassing.
I can't even find the words for it.

557
00:06:52.600 --> 00:06:54.190
Don't kill me!

558
00:06:54.190 --> 00:06:55.980
You ask the impossible.

559
00:06:59.020 --> 00:07:01.360
Stop, stop, stop!

560
00:07:01.360 --> 00:07:03.740
Stop!

561
00:07:02.070 --> 00:07:03.740
Well, well!

562
00:07:03.740 --> 00:07:06.030
Boss!

563
00:07:06.030 --> 00:07:11.290
It's so good to be working
under you again after so long!

564
00:07:08.530 --> 00:07:11.290
Galdino
Former Baroque Works Agent
(Crocodile's Subordinate)

565
00:07:11.290 --> 00:07:12.540
You bastard!

566
00:07:12.540 --> 00:07:15.410
How could you betray me like this, Galdino?!

567
00:07:15.410 --> 00:07:20.420
I don't recall ever saying
I was your subordinate, Buggy!

568
00:07:21.670 --> 00:07:24.380
You no-good ingrate!

569
00:07:24.880 --> 00:07:27.300
Call me whatever you want!

570
00:07:28.550 --> 00:07:30.680
The president's toast.

571
00:07:30.680 --> 00:07:32.720
What should we do now?

572
00:07:32.720 --> 00:07:34.480
I'll serve Crocodile!

573
00:07:37.270 --> 00:07:40.060
It's a cold world we live in.

574
00:07:41.230 --> 00:07:44.690
You pushed your luck too far!

575
00:07:44.690 --> 00:07:46.900
Here! Here!

576
00:07:50.990 --> 00:07:54.870
I hear you've lost your
Warlord perks, Hawk Eye!

577
00:07:51.160 --> 00:07:54.870
Gloom Island

578
00:07:55.290 --> 00:07:58.370
What do you want, Crocodile?

579
00:07:58.370 --> 00:08:02.290
The Marines are surrounding
this island as we speak.

580
00:08:02.290 --> 00:08:03.380
No wonder.

581
00:08:05.260 --> 00:08:06.840
At the last Reverie,

582
00:08:06.840 --> 00:08:10.340
the Seven Warlords were
stripped of their status.

583
00:08:10.340 --> 00:08:14.180
All your ties with the World Government
have officially been cut.

584
00:08:14.180 --> 00:08:18.190
Now, you're just another pirate.

585
00:08:18.190 --> 00:08:21.770
The Marines move quickly in times like these.

586
00:08:22.570 --> 00:08:26.110
You're partly to blame for what happened.

587
00:08:26.110 --> 00:08:28.200
That's ancient history.

588
00:08:30.360 --> 00:08:34.370
It's troublesome, but I have to relocate.

589
00:08:34.370 --> 00:08:36.910
Come here, then.

590
00:08:38.210 --> 00:08:40.670
That doesn't sound so bad, right?

591
00:08:41.290 --> 00:08:46.630
If we teamed up, the Marines wouldn't
take our organization lightly.

592
00:08:47.210 --> 00:08:51.890
After all, they used to call you
the Marine Hunter.

593
00:08:52.510 --> 00:08:54.930
You and I are the same.

594
00:08:55.430 --> 00:08:58.930
We don't trust others.

595
00:09:03.610 --> 00:09:05.360
What does he want?!

596
00:09:05.360 --> 00:09:06.610
I'm so scared!

597
00:09:07.110 --> 00:09:12.240
Why do I always have the worst luck?!

598
00:09:12.410 --> 00:09:14.870
Captain Buggy!

599
00:09:14.870 --> 00:09:16.240
What's the matter?!

600
00:09:16.240 --> 00:09:17.700
Go fight!

601
00:09:17.700 --> 00:09:19.660
Are you scared of the Marines?!

602
00:09:20.120 --> 00:09:22.500
These dumb lackeys!

603
00:09:22.500 --> 00:09:25.090
I'm trying to make a break for it here!

604
00:09:25.090 --> 00:09:28.840
The warships around the island
are already under attack!

605
00:09:31.340 --> 00:09:34.140
They're sinking one after another!

606
00:09:35.350 --> 00:09:36.720
The Marine ships?!

607
00:09:40.310 --> 00:09:41.890
What?!

608
00:09:41.890 --> 00:09:44.150
Who's helping us?!

609
00:09:45.440 --> 00:09:47.610
It's Crocodile!

610
00:09:54.990 --> 00:09:55.870
Outta my way.

611
00:10:02.330 --> 00:10:03.830
Fire at will!

612
00:10:10.920 --> 00:10:12.590
Sables!

613
00:10:17.810 --> 00:10:22.770
So the rumors about him serving
President Buggy were true!

614
00:10:22.770 --> 00:10:26.020
He's risking his own hide to rescue us!

615
00:10:26.020 --> 00:10:28.150
Let's hear it for President Buggy!

616
00:10:30.530 --> 00:10:33.400
I see... Crocodile came!

617
00:10:38.160 --> 00:10:41.410
He must be here to collect on my loan!

618
00:10:42.080 --> 00:10:43.500
What should I do?

619
00:10:43.500 --> 00:10:45.790
I don't have the money to pay him back!

620
00:10:45.790 --> 00:10:48.130
He's scarier than the Marines!

621
00:10:52.550 --> 00:10:54.380
I've got your number.

622
00:10:54.760 --> 00:10:56.950
I knew you'd renege on your debt.

623
00:10:57.470 --> 00:10:59.510
He really has got my number!

624
00:10:59.510 --> 00:11:00.640
Well...

625
00:11:00.640 --> 00:11:08.270
Buggy's Delivery may look like it's doing well,
but there are a lot of mouths to feed!

626
00:11:08.270 --> 00:11:12.070
And my biggest earners,
the giants, all quit recently.

627
00:11:12.570 --> 00:11:16.700
If you can't pay, we can just
sell you into slavery.

628
00:11:17.530 --> 00:11:19.780
Don't say such horrible things!

629
00:11:19.780 --> 00:11:23.450
We broke out of Impel Down together!

630
00:11:23.450 --> 00:11:24.910
Croco-bro!

631
00:11:24.910 --> 00:11:28.080
That's the reason I gave you a loan...

632
00:11:28.080 --> 00:11:29.790
but if you can't pay,

633
00:11:30.210 --> 00:11:32.000
you will take responsibility.

634
00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:33.420
Responsibility?

635
00:11:34.300 --> 00:11:37.930
I'm about to form a new company,
so I need capital now.

636
00:11:37.930 --> 00:11:40.390
N-N-N-No...

637
00:11:41.560 --> 00:11:43.180
Then...

638
00:11:43.180 --> 00:11:47.520
l-let me help with that business!

639
00:11:47.520 --> 00:11:49.900
This former Warlord of the Sea...

640
00:11:50.310 --> 00:11:52.520
will serve under you!

641
00:11:52.900 --> 00:11:53.980
Yeah?

642
00:11:53.980 --> 00:11:56.950
I'll work off my debt!

643
00:11:56.950 --> 00:12:01.700
You gotta be flashy when
setting up a new company!

644
00:12:02.240 --> 00:12:04.620
I've got the manpower you need!

645
00:12:04.620 --> 00:12:06.620
Advertising design.

646
00:12:06.620 --> 00:12:08.080
Printing.

647
00:12:08.080 --> 00:12:09.250
Distribution!

648
00:12:09.250 --> 00:12:13.800
You can work us to the bone for free!

649
00:12:14.420 --> 00:12:17.880
Is this the flyer you distributed?

650
00:12:19.720 --> 00:12:22.260
You're front and center...

651
00:12:22.260 --> 00:12:23.600
President.

652
00:12:23.600 --> 00:12:26.020
N-No!

653
00:12:26.020 --> 00:12:28.270
That isn't what I wanted!

654
00:12:28.270 --> 00:12:30.060
You're saying it wasn't deliberate?!

655
00:12:36.780 --> 00:12:39.950
I-It really wasn't my intention!

656
00:12:39.950 --> 00:12:44.410
My staff just happen to
respect me a bit too much!

657
00:12:44.410 --> 00:12:46.330
I was surprised, too!

658
00:12:48.540 --> 00:12:50.250
President!

659
00:12:50.790 --> 00:12:52.920
I made a good one!

660
00:12:53.920 --> 00:12:56.130
Hey, what the hell is that?!

661
00:12:56.130 --> 00:12:58.920
I made sure you looked the coolest!

662
00:12:58.920 --> 00:13:01.090
What?!

663
00:13:04.220 --> 00:13:06.890
You haven't shown this to anyone yet, right?

664
00:13:06.890 --> 00:13:08.730
We've already...

665
00:13:08.730 --> 00:13:10.810
...distributed it worldwide!

666
00:13:10.810 --> 00:13:13.900
What?!

667
00:13:18.990 --> 00:13:20.860
Buggy was the mastermind

668
00:13:19.280 --> 00:13:23.740
Marine Headquarters

669
00:13:20.860 --> 00:13:23.740
of the infamous Impel Down prison break...

670
00:13:23.740 --> 00:13:26.790
and a former member of
the Pirate King's crew.

671
00:13:26.790 --> 00:13:30.870
He was once on equal footing with
Red Hair, one of the Four Emperors!

672
00:13:31.830 --> 00:13:37.840
He's so well-respected that Crocodile came
to his aid at Empty Bluffs Island.

673
00:13:37.840 --> 00:13:42.550
The link between Crocodile and Mihawk
was confirmed via wiretapping.

674
00:13:44.010 --> 00:13:47.680
A number of shady groups are already
investing in "Marine hunting."

675
00:13:47.690 --> 00:13:52.900
We already have our hands full with
the recent wave of insurrections,

676
00:13:52.900 --> 00:13:55.600
which makes Cross Guild
a significant threat to us.

677
00:13:55.940 --> 00:13:58.000
What are the bounties of those three?

678
00:13:59.490 --> 00:14:01.280
The former Warlord of the Sea:

679
00:14:01.280 --> 00:14:02.780
Sir Crocodile!

680
00:14:03.410 --> 00:14:05.700
His logia fruit is formidable.

681
00:14:05.700 --> 00:14:09.200
He also has a sharp intellect
and a knack for leadership.

682
00:14:10.120 --> 00:14:13.170
His bounty is now 1 billion 965 million berries!

683
00:14:13.170 --> 00:14:15.670
Hawk Eye Mihawk!

684
00:14:15.670 --> 00:14:20.590
The ex-Warlord with even greater swordplay
than Red Hair of the Four Emperors.

685
00:14:21.220 --> 00:14:24.760
His bounty as the world's
greatest swordsman is now...

686
00:14:25.760 --> 00:14:28.390
3 billion 590 million berries!

687
00:14:28.390 --> 00:14:32.020
And Buggy the Bombastic Clown!

688
00:14:32.430 --> 00:14:34.940
We've already gone over his record,

689
00:14:34.940 --> 00:14:38.610
and now the other two yield to his authority!

690
00:14:39.820 --> 00:14:43.610
His bounty is 3 billion 189 million berries!

691
00:14:43.610 --> 00:14:47.530
Just like Straw Hat Luffy,
we consider him to be a new Emperor,

692
00:14:47.530 --> 00:14:52.540
and recognize him as a serious threat
to the World Government!

693
00:14:53.960 --> 00:14:57.210
So, you're an Emperor now?

694
00:14:57.210 --> 00:15:00.000
You've made quite a name for yourself...

695
00:15:00.000 --> 00:15:01.340
clown.

696
00:15:01.340 --> 00:15:03.170
I'm really sorry!

697
00:15:03.170 --> 00:15:04.800
So sorry!

698
00:15:04.800 --> 00:15:05.680
I'll lick your–

699
00:15:05.680 --> 00:15:06.760
Shut up!

700
00:15:08.470 --> 00:15:09.930
But...

701
00:15:09.930 --> 00:15:12.060
on the other hand,

702
00:15:12.060 --> 00:15:15.060
it's not a bad idea to have
him as our figurehead.

703
00:15:16.440 --> 00:15:18.610
I, for one...

704
00:15:18.610 --> 00:15:22.730
would rather avoid the hassle
of being an Emperor.

705
00:15:23.320 --> 00:15:25.150
You sure?

706
00:15:25.150 --> 00:15:29.740
He can have the target on his back.
We can always dispose of him later.

707
00:15:32.950 --> 00:15:35.040
You're right.

708
00:15:46.550 --> 00:15:48.010
Listen up!

709
00:15:49.140 --> 00:15:56.640
We formed Cross Guild to prepare
for the looming new age!

710
00:15:56.640 --> 00:15:59.230
Let me introduce the executives!

711
00:15:59.560 --> 00:16:01.320
First...

712
00:16:01.320 --> 00:16:04.280
Sir Crocodile!

713
00:16:07.200 --> 00:16:08.820
And...

714
00:16:09.490 --> 00:16:13.160
Hawk Eye Mihawk!

715
00:16:15.290 --> 00:16:16.540
Crocodile!

716
00:16:16.540 --> 00:16:18.250
Mihawk!

717
00:16:20.500 --> 00:16:22.000
We'll follow you!

718
00:16:22.000 --> 00:16:24.670
Sir Crocodile!

719
00:16:24.670 --> 00:16:27.970
Alright, guys!

720
00:16:27.970 --> 00:16:30.590
It's time to get flashy!

721
00:16:36.640 --> 00:16:38.890
President Buggy is crying!

722
00:16:38.890 --> 00:16:41.610
We're moved to tears, too!

723
00:16:43.400 --> 00:16:47.150
What's gonna happen to my life?!

724
00:16:47.150 --> 00:16:50.030
Near Sphinx,
Whitebeard's Homeland

New World

725
00:16:54.700 --> 00:16:57.040
I see the island, Marco.

726
00:16:57.040 --> 00:16:58.410
Right.

727
00:16:58.410 --> 00:17:00.870
I'll be off then.

728
00:17:03.250 --> 00:17:05.500
Thanks for the ride,

729
00:17:05.500 --> 00:17:06.880
Shanks.

730
00:17:06.880 --> 00:17:08.220
What?

731
00:17:08.220 --> 00:17:11.640
You mean you're not joining the crew, Marco?

732
00:17:13.180 --> 00:17:15.010
Quit dreaming.

733
00:17:19.310 --> 00:17:24.150
My days of babysitting great pirates are over!

734
00:17:24.150 --> 00:17:25.440
You jerk!

735
00:17:25.440 --> 00:17:27.440
It's not like I'm high-maintenance!

736
00:17:27.440 --> 00:17:28.440
Right, Beck?

737
00:17:28.440 --> 00:17:30.070
You are.

738
00:17:29.240 --> 00:17:30.070
What?!

739
00:17:34.200 --> 00:17:35.530
See you!

740
00:17:38.200 --> 00:17:41.120
A Short

 While Ago

 In Wano

741
00:17:48.920 --> 00:17:50.340
What?!

742
00:17:51.220 --> 00:17:53.140
You're not gonna come?!

743
00:17:53.140 --> 00:17:55.100
Be a pirate with us!

744
00:17:56.810 --> 00:17:58.810
Yamato, no!

745
00:17:58.810 --> 00:18:01.180
Say it isn't so!

746
00:18:01.180 --> 00:18:03.520
I can't imagine a day without you!

747
00:18:08.570 --> 00:18:10.990
You guys noticed it, didn't you?

748
00:18:11.360 --> 00:18:13.200
What happened with that forest guy?

749
00:18:13.740 --> 00:18:17.030
Someone's tremendous haki
saved this country.

750
00:18:17.450 --> 00:18:19.620
Kaido may be gone,

751
00:18:19.620 --> 00:18:22.500
but guys like that will now target Wano.

752
00:18:24.960 --> 00:18:26.420
I can't abandon them!

753
00:18:27.040 --> 00:18:32.260
Besides, our worries would spoil
the adventure for both of us, right?

754
00:18:32.260 --> 00:18:34.470
But I still wanna be one of you!

755
00:18:34.470 --> 00:18:36.970
To be called a crewmate!

756
00:18:38.600 --> 00:18:40.680
I get it, but...

757
00:18:46.900 --> 00:18:48.480
You're right.

758
00:18:49.480 --> 00:18:53.820
If you stayed, it'd be a load off my mind.

759
00:18:54.990 --> 00:18:58.370
Okay, I'll leave Momo and the others to you.

760
00:19:01.540 --> 00:19:06.830
But, Yamato, Momo has a lot of pride.
It'd be a pain if you wounded it.

761
00:19:06.830 --> 00:19:08.210
I know.

762
00:19:08.210 --> 00:19:10.710
I'll find another excuse to stay.

763
00:19:10.710 --> 00:19:12.670
Yamato!

764
00:19:14.050 --> 00:19:16.430
Hey, Straw Hat!

765
00:19:16.970 --> 00:19:18.550
Marco!

766
00:19:18.930 --> 00:19:24.270
There's a ship nearby that's going
my way, so I'm heading off!

767
00:19:24.270 --> 00:19:26.310
Oh, you're going!

768
00:19:26.310 --> 00:19:27.730
Yeah!

769
00:19:30.110 --> 00:19:35.450
You saved my life during
the Summit War, right?

770
00:19:35.780 --> 00:19:38.870
Take Ace's brother with you, Jinbe!

771
00:19:39.240 --> 00:19:40.620
Thank you!

772
00:19:41.080 --> 00:19:43.750
Everyone was hell-bent
on saving you back then.

773
00:19:43.750 --> 00:19:46.000
I wonder why, Jinbe?

774
00:19:46.000 --> 00:19:48.710
Well, that was ages ago.

775
00:19:48.710 --> 00:19:50.380
Who could say?

776
00:19:53.920 --> 00:19:57.630
I'm sure Ace would be proud
of how far you've come!

777
00:20:02.930 --> 00:20:05.310
You think so?

778
00:20:08.900 --> 00:20:09.940
Luffy!

779
00:20:10.440 --> 00:20:12.940
The times belong to you guys now!

780
00:20:13.900 --> 00:20:16.190
Stay strong!

781
00:20:18.780 --> 00:20:19.820
Yeah!

782
00:20:19.820 --> 00:20:21.320
See you!

783
00:20:34.460 --> 00:20:38.180
Vould you stop blaming yourself, Koala?

784
00:20:40.140 --> 00:20:42.890
Sabo will be A-OK!

785
00:20:44.180 --> 00:20:46.980
I'm just glad you're all safe.

786
00:20:46.980 --> 00:20:48.440
Vell said!

787
00:20:48.440 --> 00:20:51.060
Nothing can taint that miracle!

788
00:20:48.440 --> 00:20:49.640
Kamabakka Queendom
Grand Line

789
00:20:53.650 --> 00:20:55.110
Gosh though!

790
00:20:55.110 --> 00:21:01.240
I'll never forgive that naughty Sabo
for making us worry like this!

791
00:21:01.700 --> 00:21:04.830
It supposedly happened after we separated...

792
00:21:05.370 --> 00:21:07.700
but I still believe in him.

793
00:21:07.700 --> 00:21:14.210
You stole the words right outta my mouth!

794
00:21:14.210 --> 00:21:18.170
Hey, boy! I wanted to say that, too!

795
00:21:18.170 --> 00:21:19.670
Pipe down!

796
00:21:19.670 --> 00:21:22.050
You guys are annoying!

797
00:21:32.440 --> 00:21:34.270
Dragon, sir...

798
00:21:37.690 --> 00:21:39.360
Sabo will be fine.

799
00:21:41.570 --> 00:21:42.910
But...

800
00:21:42.910 --> 00:21:47.450
if he really killed King Cobra...

801
00:21:47.990 --> 00:21:50.790
I won't forgive him.

802
00:21:51.160 --> 00:21:53.040
No matter what his reasons were!

803
00:22:01.170 --> 00:22:03.550
Tell me, Kuma.

804
00:22:04.050 --> 00:22:05.720
What exactly...

805
00:22:06.100 --> 00:22:07.850
did you see there?

806
00:22:09.100 --> 00:22:11.600
A... A... A...

807
00:22:12.060 --> 00:22:15.190
As you wish...

808
00:22:16.520 --> 00:22:19.530
As you wish...

809
00:22:38.960 --> 00:22:41.420
Incoming call to the Kamabakka Queendom!

810
00:22:41.760 --> 00:22:43.760
It could be the Flame Emperor!

811
00:22:42.300 --> 00:22:43.760
Marine Headquarters
New World

812
00:22:44.090 --> 00:22:46.470
Record it and trace the call!

813
00:22:46.470 --> 00:22:47.550
Yes, sir!

814
00:22:53.350 --> 00:22:54.940
Everyone, quiet!

815
00:23:02.070 --> 00:23:02.990
Hello!

816
00:23:03.400 --> 00:23:04.610
This is Koala!

817
00:23:06.070 --> 00:23:07.780
It's me...

818
00:23:09.030 --> 00:23:10.330
Sabo!

819
00:23:13.710 --> 00:23:15.000
I'm sorry...

820
00:23:15.830 --> 00:23:18.080
for all the trouble.

821
00:23:43.010 --> 00:23:45.580
"Jikan gire sa"
"Time's up, won't come back"

822
00:23:46.970 --> 00:23:49.940
Dareka ga mata waratta
Somebody said again, with a laugh

823
00:23:51.090 --> 00:23:55.270
Joutou saa kakurenbo wa
Fine then, guess time for hide-and-seek's...

824
00:23:56.100 --> 00:23:57.100
Owari

825
00:23:56.300 --> 00:23:57.100
...over now

826
00:23:58.520 --> 00:24:02.500
Ikou hora
(Mou sugu mieru)
Let's go, come on
(We can see it soon)

827
00:24:02.500 --> 00:24:06.690
(Boku tachi no shima ga)

828
00:24:02.560 --> 00:24:06.260
Kodou nariki shimase
Our heartbeats were meant to sound out
(Our island)

829
00:24:06.260 --> 00:24:10.520
Nani ka ga kawaru

830
00:24:06.420 --> 00:24:10.520
Things will soon change, wait and see
(We can see it soon)

831
00:24:06.760 --> 00:24:10.520
(Mou sugu mieru)

832
00:24:10.510 --> 00:24:14.380
(1-2-3)

833
00:24:10.540 --> 00:24:14.380
Chikara zuyoku nare jikan wa aru zo
Get stronger, despair no longer, you still have time to spare

834
00:24:14.620 --> 00:24:15.810
Kakageyou
Let's raise that dream

835
00:24:15.810 --> 00:24:22.730
Kono mune afureteru kodoku dake ja ikirenai

836
00:24:15.810 --> 00:24:22.830
Living off just grief and solitude, it can't sustain a soul like mine, oh no

837
00:24:22.730 --> 00:24:26.750
Osanai bokura nara jiyuu da na

838
00:24:22.830 --> 00:24:26.750
When we were young, we were so carefree, that's all done now

839
00:24:26.800 --> 00:24:29.390
Baka na yume
What a foolish dream

840
00:24:30.280 --> 00:24:31.360
Ikiru
...we looked to

841
00:24:31.360 --> 00:24:35.070
Mienai saki wo terashite yuku
Shining a light on paths that no one's ever tread down

842
00:24:35.070 --> 00:24:39.150
Get up, on our feet and Try

843
00:24:35.410 --> 00:24:39.150
Jibun no ashi de Try##

844
00:24:39.150 --> 00:24:43.160
Let's see the ends of places no one's ever dreamed of

845
00:24:39.440 --> 00:24:43.160
Sekai no hate wo tomo ni miyou

846
00:24:43.160 --> 00:24:46.960
Yeah, together we can all Fly

847
00:24:43.500 --> 00:24:46.960
Issho nara ikeru Fly##
